# Backend Stage Zero API

A simple Go REST API that classifies users based on their name using external APIs (Agify, Genderize, Nationalize) and stores the result in an in-memory store.

---

## 🚀 Features

- Create user profile with classification data
- Fetch user by ID
- Fetch all users
- Filter users by:
  - gender
  - country_id
  - age_group
- Delete users
- Concurrent external API calls using goroutines (`errgroup`)
- In-memory data store (no database required)

---

## 📦 Tech Stack

- Go (net/http)
- UUID for IDs
- errgroup (concurrency handling)
- External APIs:
  - https://api.agify.io
  - https://api.genderize.io
  - https://api.nationalize.io

---

---

## ▶️ Running the Project Locally

Make sure Go is installed:

```bash
go version
git clone https://github.com/Taterbro/backendStageZero.git
cd backendStageZero
go mod tidy
go run main.go
```

server will start at http://localhost:8080
